Have made this 2 years in a row without the insta cure. This year, I used pickling spices that I combined and sealed last year. But the best change that I made was with a sauce. Instead of using a condiment as a side, I thickened about 2 cups of the leftover broth with Wondra (I was lazy), and flavored the sauce with Goulden's mustard -- maybe just a couple of tablespoons. So so good!

