Rating: 3
I used a 3# pre-seasoned/brined corned beef I bought from Trader Joes. I increased the boiling time to about 4 hours to get the collagen in the beef to break down--2.25 was very short, with very tough results. Adding the veggies separate was a nice step, allowing them to stay somewhat al dente instead of disintegrating into mush. The flavor profile was way on the side of bitter/anise-y with the allspice, parsnips, and turnips. If cooking for a crowd, I would dial back all 3 of those.

