I'm rating this a keeper after using a variety of brines over the past 4 or 5 years. While I was somewhat skeptical, as I usually boil and cool my brines before using, I followed the recipe corning a 8 1/2 lb grass fed Angus brisket. It was great! My Irish son-in-law blessed it and ate his share and more. Not too salty at all, but I didn't pierce the meat as directed, and brined it from Sunday to the following Saturday, cooking it that night and reheating when I cooked the vegetables in the broth before the family arrived. A keeper.

