I fell in love with natural corned beef on a schooner cruise off the coast of Maine. I left out the Insta Cure and made my own pickling spice blend (allspice berries, bay leaves, cardamom, cinnamon sticks, whole cloves, coriander seed, mustard seeds and peppercorns). My corned beef turned out delicious. I used the crock pot to cook it. There wasn't enough room for the potatoes and cabbage to cook together, so I cooked those separately--the potatoes in the crock pot after removing the corned beef and the cabbage on the stove with some of the onions and liquid from the corned beef.

