Rating: 4
This corned beef is much better than store bought. It is much more flavorful and more economical too. I like being able to control what goes into it. I did not have a problem with dryness. Both sauces were good accompaniments to the meat. Having read the reviews, I shortened the brine time to cut down on saltiness. Five days was more than enough to completely cure the brisket without making it too salty. Be very careful about reducing the amount of salt used. The salt is necessary to inhibit the growth of unpleasant (and sometimes dangerous) bacteria. Keeping the brine cold is also important but the less salt used the more likely there will be spoilage.

