Rating: 4
Wonderful!!! Well worth the effort. I used the insta cure, brined the brisket for ten days, instead of submerging the brisket in a large roasting pan I opted to place it in a air sealed plastic bag and turned it over ever day. I opted to cook it in a slow cooker, starting on high and heating to a slow boil and then cooking for two hours and then on slow for an additional four hours. It was tender, moist and very flavorful. The family thought it was the best corned beef they had ever had. It was saltier than I prefer, which might have been a result of my air seal bagging to brine it, so next time I'll reduce the salt in the brine by 1/2 a cup. But this is a keeper.

